<section class="two-column-section">
    <div class="column">
        <h1 class="section-heading">How Does it Work?</h1>
        <p>When you authorize this application through your Spotify account, you grant permission to store your Spotify
            account information in our database. Rest assured, we never ask for your password or other
            sensitive
            information. We only request permission to view your username, email, your followed
            artists, your top artists, and the ability to modify your followed artists (future features may depend on
            this).
        </p>

        <p>
            Those permissions are needed for interfacing with the <a
                href="https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api" target="_blank">Spotify Web API</a>, enabling
            us to retrieve your followed artists and their releases. Weekly Releases processes this data, filters for
            the past seven days, and sends you an email with the latest
            releases, every Friday morning.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="column">
        <h1 class="section-heading">Ending Service</h1>
        <p>If you would like to delete your data from our database, and discontinue use of this service follow these
            steps:
        </p>
